reviews.review_text: A very good 94 show Nice recording. In '94, Garcia usually either played well OR sang well, sometimes neither. He played well at this show, and the jams were great. Very jazzy and intricate Bird Song and a great Attics. I thought the Space was pretty cool too. I love all the "new" songs, let the Deadheads say little or much, and there are a lot of them on this show, and they're all well-played. Thanks!

Among the best Foolish Hearts I saw Taped the show from the tapers section and there were horrible crackles in the PA that made it unlistenable (the bitch of the East coast was that you couldn't tape FOB as often as you would like).  The Foolish Heart is beastly!  4-5 minute intro and a lovely jam all through.  16 years later I still remembered it.  And it's lovely to hear it again.  The rest of the show is rough to say the least....until the Other One>Attics>SugarMag

Foolish Heart I guess this is what passes as a 'jamming' 1990's show and there ARE moments when some interesting music is being played, but I can not hear Jerry's playing in most of this mix and when he does play some tasteful stuff, he it gives up and rest of band has to fill in. I always go to versions of 'Other One' to remind myself of what made me love this band in the first place, the energy, dynamism and sheer bravado of this late 60s song always seemed to be the purest form of experimentation, and in this show, at least,it is pretty poor. 'nuff said.

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Set 1 Highlights: Bird Song

Set 2 Highlights: All of set 2. This is a performance worthy of Giants Stadium.
